00:54:58,251 --> 00:55:00,586
It's a wonderful pet to have.

767
00:55:00,670 --> 00:55:02,588
Got you out of the laundry, though.

768
00:55:02,672 --> 00:55:04,882
Well, it might do more than that.

769
00:55:04,966 --> 00:55:07,968
How about expanding the library?
Get some new books in there.

770
00:55:08,053 --> 00:55:10,763
If you're gonna ask for something,
ask for a pool table.

771
00:55:10,847 --> 00:55:13,307
- Right.
- How do you expect to do that?

772
00:55:13,391 --> 00:55:18,646
I mean, get new books in here,
Mr. Dufresne, if you please?

773
00:55:18,730 --> 00:55:20,481
Ask the Warden for funds.

774
00:55:21,900 --> 00:55:25,194
Son, son. Six wardens
have been through here in my tenure,

775
00:55:25,278 --> 00:55:28,906
and I've learned one immutable, universal truth.

776
00:55:28,990 --> 00:55:30,699
Not one of them born...

777
00:55:30,700 --> 00:55:35,663
whose asshole wouldn't pucker up tighter than
a snare drum when you asked them for funds.

778
00:55:35,747 --> 00:55:38,040
The budget's stretched thin, as it is.

779
00:55:38,124 --> 00:55:39,375
I see.

780
00:55:39,459 --> 00:55:43,003
Perhaps I could write to the State Senate
and request funds from them.

781
00:55:43,088 --> 00:55:47,466
As far as they're concerned, there's only three
ways to spend money when it comes to prisons:

782
00:55:47,550 --> 00:55:49,635
more walls, more bars and more guards.

783
00:55:49,719 --> 00:55:54,139
Still, I'd like to try, with your permission.
A letter a week. They can't ignore me forever.

784
00:55:54,224 --> 00:55:55,766
Sure can.

785
00:55:55,850 --> 00:55:58,728
But you write your letters,
if it makes you happy.

786
00:55:58,813 --> 00:56:01,106
I'll even mail them for you. How's that?

787
00:56:03,025 --> 00:56:06,069
So, Andy started writing a letter a week,

788
00:56:06,153 --> 00:56:08,238
just like he said.

789
00:56:12,285 --> 00:56:16,413
And, just like Norton said, Andy got no answers.

790
00:56:24,255 --> 00:56:29,759
The following April, Andy did tax returns
for half the guards at Shawshank.

791
00:56:29,844 --> 00:56:32,929
The year after that, he did them all...

792
00:56:33,014 --> 00:56:35,098
including the Warden's.

793
00:56:36,475 --> 00:56:40,228
The year after that, they rescheduled
the start of the intramural season

794
00:56:40,313 --> 00:56:42,397
to coincide with tax season.

795
00:56:44,692 --> 00:56:48,903
The guards on the opposing teams
all remembered to bring their W-2s.

796
00:56:48,988 --> 00:56:53,116
So, Moresby Prison issued you your gun,
but you had to pay for it?

797
00:56:53,200 --> 00:56:54,952
Damn right. The holster, too.

798
00:56:55,037 --> 00:56:56,287
That's tax-deductible.

799
00:56:56,371 --> 00:56:57,538
You can write that off.

800
00:56:57,622 --> 00:57:00,958
Yes, sir.
Andy was a regular cottage industry.

801
00:57:01,043 --> 00:57:04,086
In fact, it got so busy at tax time...

802
00:57:04,171 --> 00:57:06,213
he was allowed a staff.

803
00:57:06,298 --> 00:57:08,758
Hey, Red, can you hand me a stack of 1040s?

804
00:57:08,842 --> 00:57:11,510
It got me out of the wood shop
a month out of the year,

805
00:57:11,595 --> 00:57:14,263
and that was fine by me.

806
00:57:14,348 --> 00:57:17,725
And still...he kept sending those letters.

807
00:57:23,023 --> 00:57:24,857
Red, Andy.

808
00:57:24,941 --> 00:57:26,150
It's Brooks.

809
00:57:26,234 --> 00:57:28,694
Watch the door.

810
00:57:28,779 --> 00:57:30,363
Please, Brooks.

811
00:57:30,447 --> 00:57:32,448
- Just calm the fuck down.
- Stay back!

812
00:57:32,532 --> 00:57:34,575
- Stay back!
- What the hell's going on?

813
00:57:34,659 --> 00:57:37,745
You tell me. One second he's fine.
Then out comes the knife.

814
00:57:37,829 --> 00:57:40,289
Brooks, we can talk about this. Right?

815
00:57:40,374 --> 00:57:42,500
Nothing to talk about, goddamn it!

816
00:57:42,584 --> 00:57:44,293
I'm gonna cut his fucking throat.

817
00:57:44,378 --> 00:57:46,253
Heywood? Wait, what's he done to you?

818
00:57:46,338 --> 00:57:48,464
It's what they done!

819
00:57:48,548 --> 00:57:49,965
I...I got no choice...

820
00:57:50,050 --> 00:57:52,719
You're not gonna hurt him.
Even Heywood knows that.

821
00:57:52,804 --> 00:57:55,430
- Right, Heywood?
- I...I know that, sure.

822
00:57:55,515 --> 00:57:58,934
You won't hurt him, because he's a friend,
and you're a reasonable man.

823
00:57:59,018 --> 00:58:00,310
That's right. Right, guys?

824
00:58:00,395 --> 00:58:03,772
- Yes.
- So, put the knife down. Brooks, look at me.

825
00:58:03,856 --> 00:58:05,690
Put the knife down.

826
00:58:06,776 --> 00:58:07,943
Brooks...

827
00:58:08,027 --> 00:58:10,278
Look at his neck, for God's sake.

828
00:58:10,363 --> 00:58:12,697
Brooks, look at his neck. It's bleeding.

829
00:58:14,033 --> 00:58:15,617
It's the only...

830
00:58:15,701 --> 00:58:17,994
It's the only way they'd let me stay.

831
00:58:18,079 --> 00:58:20,664
Come on. This is crazy.
You don't want to do this.

832
00:58:20,665 --> 00:58:22,749
Put it down.

833
00:58:30,133 --> 00:58:34,845
Come on. Take it easy.
You're going to be all right.

834
00:58:34,929 --> 00:58:36,304
Him?

835
00:58:36,389 --> 00:58:40,058
Hell, what about me?
Crazy old fool damn near cut my throat.

836
00:58:40,143 --> 00:58:42,769
Shit, Heywood,
you've had worse from shaving.

837
00:58:42,854 --> 00:58:45,105
What the hell did you do to set him off, anyway?

838
00:58:45,189 --> 00:58:47,524
Nothing. I come in here to say fare-thee-well.

839
00:58:47,608 --> 00:58:50,736
Ain't you heard? His parole's come through.

840
00:58:52,781 --> 00:58:55,908
I just don't understand what happened in there.
That's all.

841
00:58:55,993 --> 00:58:58,578
The old man's as crazy
as a rat in a tin shithouse.

842
00:58:58,662 --> 00:59:00,872
Oh, Heywood, that's enough out of you.

843
00:59:00,956 --> 00:59:03,958
- I heard he had you shitting in your pants.
- Fuck you!

844
00:59:04,042 --> 00:59:05,418
Would you knock it off?

845
00:59:05,502 --> 00:59:07,837
Brooks ain't no bug.

846
00:59:07,921 --> 00:59:09,797
He's just...

847
00:59:11,675 --> 00:59:13,509
He's just institutionalized.

848
00:59:14,845 --> 00:59:16,512
Institutionalized, my ass.

849
00:59:16,597 --> 00:59:20,892
The man's been in here 50 years, Heywood.
50 years.

850
00:59:20,976 --> 00:59:22,685
This is all he knows.

851
00:59:22,769 --> 00:59:25,188
In here, he's an important man.

852
00:59:25,272 --> 00:59:26,731
He's an educated man.

853
00:59:26,815 --> 00:59:28,900
Outside, he's nothing.

854
00:59:31,069 --> 00:59:33,696
Just a used-up con with arthritis in both hands.

855
00:59:33,780 --> 00:59:36,991
Probably couldn't get a
library card if he tried.

856
00:59:37,075 --> 00:59:39,160
You know what I'm trying to say?

857
00:59:39,244 --> 00:59:41,996
Red, I do believe you're
talking out of your ass.

858
00:59:43,248 --> 00:59:46,167
You believe whatever you want, Floyd.

859
00:59:46,168 --> 00:59:48,712
But I'm telling you, these walls are funny.

860
00:59:50,131 --> 00:59:52,216
First you hate 'em...

861
00:59:53,760 --> 00:59:55,844
..then you get used to 'em.

862
00:59:57,472 --> 01:00:00,098
Enough time passes...

863
01:00:00,183 --> 01:00:03,143
you get so you depend on 'em.

864
01:00:03,228 --> 01:00:05,562
That's institutionalized.

865
01:00:05,647 --> 01:00:07,022
Shit.

866
01:00:07,023 --> 01:00:08,649
You can never get like that.

867
01:00:08,733 --> 01:00:10,651
Oh, yeah?

868
01:00:10,735 --> 01:00:13,320
Say that when you've been here
as long as Brooks has.

869
01:00:13,404 --> 01:00:15,280
Goddamn right.

870
01:00:17,617 --> 01:00:20,160
They send you here for life.

871
01:00:20,245 --> 01:00:22,329
That's exactly what they take.

872
01:00:24,249 --> 01:00:26,333
The part that counts, anyway.

873
01:00:33,841 --> 01:00:36,009
I can't take care of you no more, Jake.

874
01:00:37,929 --> 01:00:39,763
You go on, now.

875
01:00:40,848 --> 01:00:45,519
You're free.

876
01:01:01,412 --> 01:01:03,288
Bye.

877
01:01:04,373 --> 01:01:06,291
Good luck, Brooks.

878
01:01:42,870 --> 01:01:45,581
Dear fellas...

879
01:01:45,665 --> 01:01:49,877
I can't believe
how fast things move on the outside.

880
01:01:51,296 --> 01:01:54,340
Watch it, old-timer! Are
you trying to get killed?

881
01:01:54,424 --> 01:01:57,760
I saw an automobile once, when I was a kid,

882
01:01:57,844 --> 01:02:00,763
but now...they're everywhere.

883
01:02:04,976 --> 01:02:08,562
The world went and got itself
in a big damn hurry.

884
01:02:24,913 --> 01:02:31,210
The parole board got me into
this halfway house called The Brewer,

885
01:02:31,294 --> 01:02:35,089
and a job bagging groceries at the Foodway.

886
01:02:37,133 --> 01:02:42,471
It's hard work, and I try to keep up,
but my hands hurt most of the time.

887
01:02:42,556 --> 01:02:44,557
Make sure your man double-bags.

888
01:02:44,642 --> 01:02:46,893
Last time, the bottom near came out.

889
01:02:46,977 --> 01:02:50,271
Make sure you double-bag, like the lady says.
Understand?

890
01:02:50,356 --> 01:02:51,815
Yes, sir. I surely will.

891
01:02:51,899 --> 01:02:55,694
I don't think
the store manager likes me very much.

892
01:02:58,656 --> 01:03:03,451
Sometimes, after work,
I go to the park and feed the birds.

893
01:03:03,536 --> 01:03:08,873
I keep thinking Jake might just show up
and say hello.

894
01:03:08,958 --> 01:03:10,750
But he never does.

895
01:03:11,836 --> 01:03:17,215
And I hope, wherever he is,
he's doing OK and making new friends.

896
01:03:20,720 --> 01:03:23,638
I have trouble sleeping at night.

897
01:03:23,723 --> 01:03:26,516
I have bad dreams, like I'm falling.

898
01:03:27,601 --> 01:03:29,519
I wake up, scared.

899
01:03:29,603 --> 01:03:33,606
Sometimes it takes me a while
to remember where I am.

900
01:03:35,234 --> 01:03:36,693
Maybe I should get me a gun

901
01:03:36,777 --> 01:03:40,656
and rob the Foodway, so they'd send me home.

902
01:03:40,741 --> 01:03:43,075
I could shoot the manager, while I was at it.

903
01:03:43,160 --> 01:03:45,119
Sort of like a bonus.

904
01:03:46,621 --> 01:03:50,875
I guess I'm too old for that sort of nonsense
any more.

905
01:03:50,959 --> 01:03:53,002
I don't like it here.

906
01:03:53,086 --> 01:03:55,755
I'm tired of being afraid all the time.

907
01:03:55,839 --> 01:03:56,922
I've decided...

908
01:03:57,007 --> 01:03:58,883
not to stay.

909
01:04:10,228 --> 01:04:13,731
I doubt they'll kick up any fuss.

910
01:04:13,815 --> 01:04:15,900
Not for an old crook like me.

911
01:05:18,923 --> 01:05:22,968
"I doubt they'll kick up any fuss.
Not for an old crook like me.

912
01:05:24,136 --> 01:05:28,181
PS. Tell Heywood
I'm sorry I put a knife to his throat.

913
01:05:28,182 --> 01:05:30,267
No hard feelings. Brooks."

914
01:05:40,988 --> 01:05:43,072
He should have died in here.

915
01:05:48,495 --> 01:05:52,957
What the fuck have you done?
It's a goddamn mess. I'll tell you that.

916
01:05:57,671 --> 01:05:59,088
What's all this?

917
01:05:59,172 --> 01:06:03,050
You tell me, fuck-stick.
They're all addressed to you.

918
01:06:03,135 --> 01:06:04,427
Take it.

919
01:06:13,395 --> 01:06:14,979
"Dear Mr. Dufresne...

920
01:06:16,064 --> 01:06:18,065
In response to your repeated enquiries,

921
01:06:18,150 --> 01:06:22,862
the State has allocated the enclosed funds
for your library project."

922
01:06:22,946 --> 01:06:24,322
This is 200 dollars.

923
01:06:25,365 --> 01:06:29,285
"In addition, the Library District
has generously responded

924
01:06:29,369 --> 01:06:32,079
with a charitable donation
of used books and sundries.

925
01:06:32,164 --> 01:06:34,248
We trust this will fill your needs.

926
01:06:34,333 --> 01:06:38,462
We now consider the matter closed.
Please stop sending us letters."

927
01:06:38,546 --> 01:06:41,381
I want all this cleared out
before the Warden gets back.

928
01:06:41,466 --> 01:06:43,133
Yes, sir.

929
01:06:46,888 --> 01:06:48,263
Good for you, Andy.

930
01:06:50,892 --> 01:06:52,351
Wow!

931
01:06:53,436 --> 01:06:55,520
It only took six years.

932
01:06:56,814 --> 01:06:59,691
From now on,
I'll write two letters a week, instead of one.

933
01:06:59,776 --> 01:07:03,320
Oh, I believe you're crazy enough.
You'd better get all this stuff out,

934
01:07:03,404 --> 01:07:04,571
like the Captain said.

935
01:07:04,656 --> 01:07:08,533
Now, I'm gonna go pinch a loaf.
When I come back, this is all gone, right?

936
01:07:14,707 --> 01:07:16,708
Wow.

937
01:07:46,782 --> 01:07:49,492
Duettino from The Marriage Of Figaro

938
01:07:50,953 --> 01:07:53,538
? Sull'aria...

939
01:07:57,167 --> 01:07:58,167
Andy,

940
01:07:58,252 --> 01:07:59,585
do you hear that?

941
01:07:59,670 --> 01:08:03,381
?..zeffiretto

942
01:08:15,602 --> 01:08:23,443
? Questa será spirera

943
01:08:53,850 --> 01:08:58,145
? Sotto i pini

944
01:08:58,229 --> 01:09:03,442
? Del boschetto

945
01:09:04,944 --> 01:09:07,321
? Sotto i pini...

946
01:09:07,405 --> 01:09:10,282
Dufresne?

947
01:09:10,366 --> 01:09:11,950
Dufresne?

948
01:09:12,035 --> 01:09:14,119
Andy, let me out.

949
01:09:16,831 --> 01:09:20,375
Andy?

950
01:09:20,460 --> 01:09:25,631
I have no idea to this day what those
two Italian ladies were singing about.

951
01:09:25,715 --> 01:09:28,133
The truth is, I don't want to know.

952
01:09:28,218 --> 01:09:30,303
Some things are best left unsaid.

953
01:09:34,350 --> 01:09:36,872
I like to think they were
singing about something

954
01:09:36,873 --> 01:09:39,395
so beautiful, it can't be expressed in words...

955
01:09:39,480 --> 01:09:41,856
and makes your heart ache because of it.

956
01:09:44,068 --> 01:09:46,778
I tell you, those voices soared...

957
01:09:46,862 --> 01:09:51,407
higher and farther
than anybody in a grey place dares to dream.

958
01:09:51,492 --> 01:09:54,869
It was like some beautiful bird
flapped into our drab little cage

959
01:09:54,954 --> 01:09:58,081
and made those walls dissolve away.

960
01:09:58,165 --> 01:10:00,500
And for the briefest of moments...

961
01:10:00,584 --> 01:10:03,670
every last man at Shawshank felt free.

962
01:10:06,173 --> 01:10:08,675
It pissed the Warden off something awful.

963
01:10:10,094 --> 01:10:11,219
Open the door.

964
01:10:13,973 --> 01:10:15,890
Open it up!

965
01:10:17,101 --> 01:10:19,477
Dufresne, open this door!

966
01:10:21,105 --> 01:10:22,438
Turn that off!

967
01:10:29,239 --> 01:10:31,991
I am warning you, Dufresne. Turn that off!

968
01:10:45,839 --> 01:10:47,715
Dufresne...

969
01:10:48,842 --> 01:10:50,926
You're mine now.

970
01:10:58,476 --> 01:11:01,228
Andy got two weeks in the hole
for that little stunt.

971
01:11:01,313 --> 01:11:03,731
On your feet!

972
01:11:04,941 --> 01:11:07,026
- Hey, look who's here.
- Maestro!

973
01:11:08,528 --> 01:11:12,573
Y- Y-You couldn't play something good, huh?
Hank Williams or something?

974
01:11:12,657 --> 01:11:15,326
They broke the door down
before I could take requests.

975
01:11:15,410 --> 01:11:17,203
Was it worth it, two weeks in the hole?

976
01:11:17,287 --> 01:11:18,537
Easiest time I ever did.

977
01:11:18,622 --> 01:11:21,665
Bullshit!
There's no such thing as easy time in the hole.

978
01:11:21,666 --> 01:11:24,293
A week in the hole is like a year.

979
01:11:24,377 --> 01:11:27,088
I had Mr. Mozart to keep me company.

980
01:11:27,173 --> 01:11:30,508
So, they let you tote that record player
down there, huh?

981
01:11:32,637 --> 01:11:34,262
It was in here.

982
01:11:34,347 --> 01:11:36,014
And in here.

983
01:11:37,225 --> 01:11:41,478
That's the beauty of music.
They can't get that from you.

984
01:11:45,399 --> 01:11:47,901
Haven't you ever felt that way about music?

985
01:11:49,570 --> 01:11:53,657
Well, I played a mean harmonica,
as a younger man.

986
01:11:53,741 --> 01:11:55,533
Lost interest in it, though.

987
01:11:55,618 --> 01:11:57,452
Didn't make much sense in here.

988
01:11:57,536 --> 01:11:59,996
Here's where it makes the most sense.

989
01:12:00,081 --> 01:12:02,666
You need it, so you don't forget.

990
01:12:02,750 --> 01:12:04,084
Forget?

991
01:12:04,168 --> 01:12:06,127
Forget that...

992
01:12:06,212 --> 01:12:08,296
there are places...

993
01:12:09,632 --> 01:12:12,175
..in the world that aren't made out of stone...

994
01:12:12,260 --> 01:12:14,302
that there's a...

995
01:12:14,387 --> 01:12:16,221
there's something...

996
01:12:16,305 --> 01:12:19,099
inside that they can't get to...

997
01:12:19,183 --> 01:12:21,476
that they can't touch.

998
01:12:21,560 --> 01:12:23,437
It's yours.

999
01:12:24,856 --> 01:12:26,565
What are you talking about?

1000
01:12:27,651 --> 01:12:29,235
Hope.

1001
01:12:29,319 --> 01:12:31,195
Hope?

1002
01:12:33,031 --> 01:12:35,700
Let me tell you something, my friend.

1003
01:12:35,784 --> 01:12:37,743
Hope is a dangerous thing.

1004
01:12:39,329 --> 01:12:41,372
Hope can drive a man insane.

1005
01:12:42,416 --> 01:12:44,333
It's got no use on the inside.

1006
01:12:44,418 --> 01:12:47,086
You'd better get used to that idea.

1007
01:12:49,506 --> 01:12:51,132
Like Brooks did?

1008
01:13:16,366 --> 01:13:17,408
Sit down.

1009
01:13:22,623 --> 01:13:26,084
It says here that you've served
30 years of a life sentence.

1010
01:13:26,169 --> 01:13:28,795
You feel you've been rehabilitated?

1011
01:13:28,880 --> 01:13:30,964
Oh, yes, sir.

1012
01:13:30,965 --> 01:13:33,050
Without a doubt.

1013
01:13:34,093 --> 01:13:36,428
And I can honestly say I'm a changed man.

1014
01:13:39,015 --> 01:13:41,058
No danger to society here.

1015
01:13:41,142 --> 01:13:43,226
God's honest truth.

1016
01:13:45,563 --> 01:13:47,647
Absolutely rehabilitated.

1017
01:13:57,575 --> 01:13:59,659
30 years.

1018
01:14:00,745 --> 01:14:02,788
Jesus, when they say it like that...

1019
01:14:02,872 --> 01:14:04,956
You wonder where it went.

1020
01:14:07,919 --> 01:14:10,003
I wonder where ten years went.

1021
01:14:15,051 --> 01:14:16,343
Here.

1022
01:14:16,427 --> 01:14:18,595
Little parole rejection present.

1023
01:14:20,432 --> 01:14:22,475
Go ahead and open it.

1024
01:14:22,559 --> 01:14:26,354
I had to go through one of your competitors.
I hope you don't mind.

1025
01:14:26,438 --> 01:14:28,523
I wanted it to be a surprise.

1026
01:14:38,659 --> 01:14:40,743
It's very pretty, Andy.

1027
01:14:41,829 --> 01:14:43,913
Thank you.

1028
01:14:45,666 --> 01:14:47,750
Are you going to play it?

1029
01:14:51,880 --> 01:14:53,965
No.

1030
01:14:56,260 --> 01:14:58,344
Not right now.

1031
01:15:05,602 --> 01:15:07,687
Tier 3 South. Clear.

1032
01:15:08,730 --> 01:15:10,773
Tier 4 North. Clear.

1033
01:15:10,858 --> 01:15:12,942
Tier 1 South. Clear.

1034
01:15:15,779 --> 01:15:17,865
Fall in!

1035
01:15:52,442 --> 01:15:54,026
Lights out!

1036
01:16:28,938 --> 01:16:30,980
Andy was as good as his word.

1037
01:16:31,065 --> 01:16:33,566
He wrote two letters a week instead of one.

1038
01:16:36,195 --> 01:16:40,323
In 1959, the State Senate
finally clued into the fact

1039
01:16:40,407 --> 01:16:43,284
they couldn't buy him off
with just a $200 check.

1040
01:16:43,369 --> 01:16:49,958
Appropriations Committee voted
an annual payment of $500 just to shut him up.

1041
01:16:50,042 --> 01:16:51,751
And you'd be amazed

1042
01:16:51,835 --> 01:16:53,503
how far Andy could stretch it.

1043
01:16:53,587 --> 01:16:56,464
He made deals with book clubs, charity groups.

1044
01:16:56,549 --> 01:16:58,925
He bought remaindered books by the pound.

1045
01:16:59,009 --> 01:17:01,219
Treasure Island.

1046
01:17:01,303 --> 01:17:03,471
Robert Louis...

1047
01:17:03,556 --> 01:17:04,764
..Stevenson.

1048
01:17:04,848 --> 01:17:06,307
Fiction, adventure.

1049
01:17:08,310 --> 01:17:09,936
What's next?

1050
01:17:09,937 --> 01:17:12,647
I got here Auto Repair and...

1051
01:17:13,692 --> 01:17:15,025
..Soap Carving.

1052
01:17:15,110 --> 01:17:18,487
Trade skills and hobbies. Goes under
Educational. The stack behind you.

1053
01:17:18,572 --> 01:17:20,614
The Count Of Monte Crisco.

1054
01:17:20,699 --> 01:17:23,033
That's Cristo, you dumb shit.

1055
01:17:23,118 --> 01:17:26,912
By Alexandree...Dumass.

1056
01:17:26,997 --> 01:17:31,917
Dumb-ass?

1057
01:17:34,421 --> 01:17:36,755
Dumas. You know what that's about?

1058
01:17:36,840 --> 01:17:38,215
Uh-uh.

1059
01:17:38,300 --> 01:17:41,010
You'll like it. It's about a prison break.

1060
01:17:41,094 --> 01:17:45,097
We ought to file that under Educational, too,
oughtn't we?

1061
01:17:45,181 --> 01:17:49,351
The rest of us did our best to pitch in
when and where we could.

1062
01:17:50,604 --> 01:17:52,438
By the year Kennedy was shot,

1063
01:17:52,522 --> 01:17:56,859
Andy had transformed a storage room
smelling of rat turds and turpentine

1064
01:17:56,860 --> 01:18:00,195
into the best prison library in New England,

1065
01:18:00,280 --> 01:18:04,158
complete with a fine selection of Hank Williams.

1066
01:18:04,242 --> 01:18:08,412
? Lawd I don't know what I'll do-ooo

1067
01:18:08,496 --> 01:18:11,248
? All I do is sit and sigh...

1068
01:18:11,333 --> 01:18:16,087
That was also the year Warden Norton
instituted his famous Inside Out program.

1069
01:18:16,172 --> 01:18:18,882
You may remember reading about it.

1070
01:18:18,966 --> 01:18:22,385
It made all the papers
and got his picture in Look Magazine.

1071
01:18:22,470 --> 01:18:24,137
No free ride.

1072
01:18:24,221 --> 01:18:27,182
But rather a genuine, progressive advance

1073
01:18:27,266 --> 01:18:29,434
in corrections and rehabilitation.

1074
01:18:30,478 --> 01:18:32,812
Our inmates, properly supervised,

1075
01:18:32,897 --> 01:18:35,649
will be put to work outside these walls,

1076
01:18:35,733 --> 01:18:37,817
performing all manner of public service.

1077
01:18:37,902 --> 01:18:41,821
These men can learn
the value of an honest day's labor,

1078
01:18:41,906 --> 01:18:45,575
while providing a valuable service
to the community and...

1079
01:18:45,660 --> 01:18:50,872
at a bare minimum of expense
to Mr. and Mrs. John Q Taxpayer.

1080
01:18:50,956 --> 01:18:53,625
Of course,
Norton failed to mention to the press

1081
01:18:53,709 --> 01:18:57,003
that "bare minimum of expense"
is a fairly loose term.

1082
01:18:57,088 --> 01:19:00,256
There are a hundred different ways
to skim off the top.

1083
01:19:00,341 --> 01:19:02,967
Men, materials, you name it.

1084
01:19:04,011 --> 01:19:06,763
And, oh, my Lord, how the money rolled in.

1085
01:19:06,847 --> 01:19:08,973
If this keeps up, you'll put me out of business.

1086
01:19:09,058 --> 01:19:11,227
- Ned!
- This pool of slave labor you've got,

1087
01:19:11,311 --> 01:19:13,354
you can underbid any contractor in town.

1088
01:19:13,438 --> 01:19:17,400
Ned, we're providing
a valuable community service here.

1089
01:19:17,484 --> 01:19:19,735
Well, that's fine for the papers

1090
01:19:19,820 --> 01:19:21,320
but I've got a family to feed.

1091
01:19:21,405 --> 01:19:23,114
Sam...

1092
01:19:23,198 --> 01:19:25,658
Sam, we go back a long way.

1093
01:19:25,742 --> 01:19:28,077
I need this new highway contract.

1094
01:19:28,161 --> 01:19:30,371
I don't get it, and I go under.

1095
01:19:30,455 --> 01:19:32,498
That's a fact.

1096
01:19:32,582 --> 01:19:34,667
You just have some of this fine pie

1097
01:19:34,751 --> 01:19:36,794
my missus made especially for you,

1098
01:19:36,878 --> 01:19:38,212
and you think about that.

1099
01:19:46,263 --> 01:19:49,181
Ned, I wouldn't worry too much
about this contract.

1100
01:19:49,266 --> 01:19:52,476
It seems to me I already got
my boys committed elsewhere.

1101
01:19:54,354 --> 01:19:56,939
You be sure and thank Maisie for this fine pie.

1102
01:19:58,567 --> 01:20:00,735
And behind every shady deal,

1103
01:20:00,819 --> 01:20:03,028
behind every dollar earned,

1104
01:20:03,113 --> 01:20:06,282
there was Andy, keeping the books.

1105
01:20:07,325 --> 01:20:10,746
Two deposits.
Maine National and New England First.

1106
01:20:10,830 --> 01:20:12,914
Night drops as always, sir.

1107
01:20:43,321 --> 01:20:45,071
Get my stuff down to the laundry.

1108
01:20:45,156 --> 01:20:47,949
- Two suits for dry-clean and a bag of whatnot.
- Yes, sir.

1109
01:20:48,034 --> 01:20:51,787
Tell them if they over-starch my shirts again,
they'll hear about it from me.

1110
01:20:51,871 --> 01:20:53,872
How do I look?

1111
01:20:53,956 --> 01:20:56,666
- Very nice, sir.
- Big charity to-do up Portland way.

1112
01:20:56,751 --> 01:20:58,460
The Governor's going to be there.

1113
01:20:59,879 --> 01:21:01,922
Want the rest of this?

1114
01:21:02,006 --> 01:21:04,090
The woman can't bake worth shit.

1115
01:21:05,468 --> 01:21:07,261
Thank you, sir.

1116
01:21:09,431 --> 01:21:13,184
- He's got his fingers in a lot of pies, I hear.
- What you hear isn't half of it.

1117
01:21:13,268 --> 01:21:15,728
He's got scams you haven't even dreamed of.

1118
01:21:15,813 --> 01:21:17,855
Kickbacks on his kickbacks.

1119
01:21:17,940 --> 01:21:20,817
There's a river of dirty money
running through this place.

1120
01:21:20,901 --> 01:21:24,153
But the problem with having all that money
is you'll have to explain

1121
01:21:24,238 --> 01:21:26,823
- where it came from.
- That's where I come in.

1122
01:21:26,907 --> 01:21:29,408
I channel it, filter it, funnel it.

1123
01:21:29,493 --> 01:21:32,036
Stocks, securities, tax-free municipals.

1124
01:21:32,120 --> 01:21:34,789
I send that money out into the real world.

1125
01:21:34,873 --> 01:21:38,501
- And when it comes back...
- Clean as a virgin's honey pot, huh?

1126
01:21:38,585 --> 01:21:39,794
Cleaner.

1127
01:21:39,878 --> 01:21:43,506
By the time Norton retires,
I'll have made him a millionaire.

1128
01:21:46,260 --> 01:21:50,680
If they ever catch on, though, he's gonna
wind up in here wearing a number himself.

1129
01:21:50,764 --> 01:21:54,016
Now, Red, I thought you had
a little more faith in me than that.

1130
01:21:54,101 --> 01:21:57,395
I know you're good, Andy,
but all that paper leaves a trail.

1131
01:21:57,479 --> 01:22:00,481
Now, anybody gets curious,
the FBI, the IRS, whatever,

1132
01:22:00,566 --> 01:22:03,401
it's gonna lead to somebody.

1133
01:22:03,485 --> 01:22:05,445
Sure it is. But not to me.

1134
01:22:05,530 --> 01:22:07,531
And certainly not to the Warden.

1135
01:22:11,578 --> 01:22:12,870
All right. Who?

1136
01:22:12,954 --> 01:22:14,663
Randall Stevens.

1137
01:22:14,747 --> 01:22:15,914
Who?

1138
01:22:17,000 --> 01:22:21,712
The silent silent partner. He's the guilty one,
Your Honor. The man with the bank accounts.

1139
01:22:21,796 --> 01:22:23,964
That's where the filtering process starts.

1140
01:22:24,048 --> 01:22:27,217
If they trace anything,
it's just going to lead to him.

1141
01:22:27,302 --> 01:22:28,886
But who is he?

1142
01:22:28,970 --> 01:22:31,013
He's a phantom, an apparition.

1143
01:22:31,097 --> 01:22:33,056
Second cousin to Harvey the Rabbit.

1144
01:22:33,141 --> 01:22:35,309
I conjured him...

1145
01:22:35,393 --> 01:22:37,436
out of thin air.

1146
01:22:37,520 --> 01:22:40,355
He doesn't exist, except on paper.

1147
01:22:43,484 --> 01:22:45,861
Andy, you canâ€™t just make a person up.

1148
01:22:45,945 --> 01:22:49,072
Sure you can, if you know how
the system works, where the cracks are.

1149
01:22:49,157 --> 01:22:52,659
It's amazing what you can accomplish by mail.

1150
01:22:52,744 --> 01:22:55,370
Mr. Stevens has a birth certificate,

1151
01:22:55,455 --> 01:22:57,789
a driver's license, social security number.

1152
01:22:57,874 --> 01:22:59,082
You're shitting me?

1153
01:22:59,167 --> 01:23:01,126
If they ever trace any of those accounts,

1154
01:23:01,210 --> 01:23:04,088
they're going to wind up chasing
a figment of my imagination.

1155
01:23:04,173 --> 01:23:06,257
Well, I'll be damned.

1156
01:23:07,551 --> 01:23:09,594
Did I say you were good?

1157
01:23:09,678 --> 01:23:11,846
Shit, you're a Rembrandt!

1158
01:23:11,931 --> 01:23:13,973
You know, the funny thing is,

1159
01:23:14,058 --> 01:23:18,019
on the outside, I was an honest man,
straight as an arrow.

1160
01:23:19,063 --> 01:23:21,439
I had to come to prison to be a crook.

1161
01:23:30,199 --> 01:23:31,574
Ever bother you?

1162
01:23:32,618 --> 01:23:36,037
I don't run the scams, Red,
I just process the profits.

1163
01:23:36,121 --> 01:23:38,164
Fine line maybe but...

1164
01:23:38,248 --> 01:23:40,959
I also built that library

1165
01:23:41,043 --> 01:23:43,670
and used it to help a dozen guys
get a high school diploma.

1166
01:23:43,754 --> 01:23:45,630
Why do you think the Warden lets me do it?

1167
01:23:45,714 --> 01:23:48,466
To keep you happy and doing the laundry.

1168
01:23:48,550 --> 01:23:50,677
Money instead of sheets.

1169
01:23:50,761 --> 01:23:53,471
Well, I work cheap. That's the trade-off.

1170
01:23:59,061 --> 01:24:01,271
Willy And The Hand Jive

1171
01:24:09,072 --> 01:24:10,864
? I know a cat named...

1172
01:24:10,949 --> 01:24:13,617
Tommy Williams
came to Shawshank in 1965

1173
01:24:13,702 --> 01:24:15,744
on a two-year stretch for B&E.

1174
01:24:15,829 --> 01:24:17,955
That's breaking and entering to you.

1175
01:24:18,039 --> 01:24:22,668
The cops caught him sneaking TV sets
out the back door of a JC Penney.

1176
01:24:22,752 --> 01:24:24,503
Young punk.

1177
01:24:24,587 --> 01:24:26,630
Mr. Rock'n'roll.

1178
01:24:26,715 --> 01:24:28,382
Cocky as hell.

1179
01:24:28,466 --> 01:24:31,051
Hey, come on, old boys! Moving like molasses!

1180
01:24:31,136 --> 01:24:33,095
Making me look bad.

1181
01:24:33,096 --> 01:24:35,055
We liked him immediately.

1182
01:24:35,140 --> 01:24:37,182
So I'm backing out the door, right?

1183
01:24:37,267 --> 01:24:38,976
And I got the TV like this.

1184
01:24:39,060 --> 01:24:42,896
It was a big old thing. I couldn't see shit.
Suddenly, I hears this voice.

1185
01:24:42,981 --> 01:24:45,024
"Freeze, kid! Hands in the air."

1186
01:24:45,108 --> 01:24:46,775
Well, I just stand there,

1187
01:24:46,860 --> 01:24:49,653
holding onto that TV.
So, finally, the voice says,

1188
01:24:49,738 --> 01:24:51,697
"Do you hear what I said, boy?"

1189
01:24:51,781 --> 01:24:54,158
I say, "Yes, sir, I sure did.

1190
01:24:54,242 --> 01:24:57,870
But if I drop this fucking thing,
you got me on destruction of property, too."

1191
01:25:01,959 --> 01:25:04,669
Hey, you've done a stretch in Cashman, right?

1192
01:25:04,754 --> 01:25:08,590
Yeah. Yeah, that was an easy piece of time,
let me tell you.

1193
01:25:08,674 --> 01:25:11,301
Weekend furloughs, work programs.

1194
01:25:11,385 --> 01:25:12,802
Not like here.

1195
01:25:12,887 --> 01:25:15,221
Sounds like you done time
all over New England.

1196
01:25:15,306 --> 01:25:20,393
Yeah, I've been in and out since I was 13. You
name the place, chances are I've been there.

1197
01:25:20,478 --> 01:25:24,481
Perhaps it's time you tried a new profession?

1198
01:25:24,565 --> 01:25:29,652
What I mean is, you don't seem to be a good
thief. Maybe you should try something else.

1199
01:25:29,737 --> 01:25:33,573
Yeah, well, what the hell
do you know about it, Capone?

1200
01:25:33,657 --> 01:25:35,408
What are you in for?

1201
01:25:35,493 --> 01:25:37,118
Me?

1202
01:25:38,621 --> 01:25:40,705
The lawyer fucked me.

1203
01:25:44,418 --> 01:25:47,837
Everybody's innocent in here.
Don't you know that?

1204
01:25:55,304 --> 01:25:59,475
As it turned out, Tommy had himself
a young wife and a new baby girl.

1205
01:26:00,519 --> 01:26:03,083
Maybe it was the thought of them on the streets

1206
01:26:03,084 --> 01:26:05,648
or his child growing up not knowing her daddy.

1207
01:26:05,732 --> 01:26:09,568
Whatever it was,
something lit a fire under that boy's ass.

1208
01:26:13,532 --> 01:26:16,784
I was thinking of maybe
trying for my high school equivalency.

1209
01:26:16,868 --> 01:26:19,453
I hear you helped a couple of fellas with that.

1210
01:26:20,664 --> 01:26:22,873
I don't waste time on losers, Tommy.

1211
01:26:24,459 --> 01:26:26,544
I ain't no goddamn loser.

1212
01:26:28,380 --> 01:26:30,464
- You mean that?
- Yeah.

1213
01:26:32,134 --> 01:26:34,176
You really mean that?

1214
01:26:34,261 --> 01:26:35,928
Yes, sir, I do.

1215
01:26:36,012 --> 01:26:38,139
Good. Because if we do this,

1216
01:26:38,223 --> 01:26:40,975
we do it all the way, 100%, nothing half-assed.

1217
01:26:42,102 --> 01:26:44,186
The thing is, see...

1218
01:26:45,355 --> 01:26:47,189
..I don't read so good.

1219
01:26:48,316 --> 01:26:49,525
Well.

1220
01:26:51,278 --> 01:26:53,320
You don't read...

1221
01:26:53,405 --> 01:26:55,490
so well.

1222
01:26:56,951 --> 01:26:58,618
We'll get to that.

1223
01:26:59,704 --> 01:27:01,454
- R.
- R...

1224
01:27:01,539 --> 01:27:02,914
- S.
- S...

1225
01:27:02,999 --> 01:27:05,167
So Andy took Tommy under his wing.

1226
01:27:05,251 --> 01:27:07,669
He started walking him through his ABCs.

1227
01:27:09,338 --> 01:27:11,923
Tommy took to it pretty well, too.

1228
01:27:12,008 --> 01:27:14,968
The boy found brains he never knew he had.

1229
01:27:17,305 --> 01:27:21,099
Before long, Andy started him
on his course requirements.

1230
01:27:21,184 --> 01:27:23,143
He really liked the kid.

1231
01:27:23,227 --> 01:27:26,396
It gave him a thrill to help a youngster
crawl off the shit heap.

1232
01:27:27,440 --> 01:27:29,482
But that wasn't the only reason.

1233
01:27:29,567 --> 01:27:32,027
Prison time is slow time.

1234
01:27:33,070 --> 01:27:35,322
So you do what you can to keep going.

1235
01:27:35,406 --> 01:27:37,657
Some fellas collect stamps.

1236
01:27:37,658 --> 01:27:40,285
Others build matchstick houses.

1237
01:27:41,329 --> 01:27:43,705
Andy built a library.

1238
01:27:44,749 --> 01:27:46,791
Now he needed a new project.

1239
01:27:46,876 --> 01:27:48,919
Tommy was it.

1240
01:27:49,003 --> 01:27:53,216
It was the same reason he spent years
shaping and polishing those rocks.

1241
01:27:53,300 --> 01:27:56,928
The same reason
he hung his fantasy girlies on the wall.

1242
01:27:58,305 --> 01:27:59,805
In prison,

1243
01:27:59,890 --> 01:28:03,017
a man will do most anything
to keep his mind occupied.

1244
01:28:04,478 --> 01:28:08,940
By 1966, right about the time
Tommy was getting ready to take his exams,

1245
01:28:08,941 --> 01:28:10,983
it was lovely Raquel.

1246
01:28:28,252 --> 01:28:29,293
Time.

1247
01:28:35,300 --> 01:28:36,592
Well?

1248
01:28:37,678 --> 01:28:39,220
Well, it's for shit.

1249
01:28:39,304 --> 01:28:41,806
I wasted a whole fucking year of my time

1250
01:28:41,890 --> 01:28:45,059
- with this bullshit.
- It's probably not as bad as you think.

1251
01:28:45,143 --> 01:28:48,854
It's worse. I didn't get one thing right.
It might as well have been in Chinese.

1252
01:28:48,939 --> 01:28:51,441
Let's see how the score comes out.

1253
01:28:51,526 --> 01:28:54,152
Well, I'll tell you how the goddamn score
comes out.

1254
01:28:55,947 --> 01:28:57,864
Two points right there.

1255
01:28:57,949 --> 01:28:59,741
There's your goddamn score!

1256
01:28:59,826 --> 01:29:03,662
Goddamn cats crawling up trees,
5x5 is 25.

1257
01:29:04,747 --> 01:29:06,290
Fuck this place!

1258
01:29:06,291 --> 01:29:07,582
Fuck it!

1259
01:29:26,394 --> 01:29:29,146
I feel bad. I let him down.

1260
01:29:29,230 --> 01:29:31,315
Ah, that's crap, kid.

1261
01:29:31,316 --> 01:29:32,858
He's proud of you.

1262
